# Front-end conventions (Testrix renderer)

These rules apply to **`src/app/**`** and **`src/styles/**`.** They **replace** generic React/Tailwind guidance for this repository.

## Stack

- **Angular** templates + **SCSS** + **`--tx-*` tokens**. Do **not** add Tailwind, Shadcn, or Radix unless the maintainer explicitly changes stack.
- See **`use-shared-ui.mdc`** (mandatory shared kit) and **`theme-and-shared-ui.mdc`** for token/widget boundaries.

## TypeScript / templates

- Prefer **early returns** in helpers and IPC-related services.
- Name UI event handlers **`handle*`** (`handleClick`, `handleSubmit`) to match existing components.
- Use **`const`** for stable callbacks passed into templates where it improves clarity.

## Accessibility

- Use **semantic HTML** and meaningful **`aria-label` / `title`** on icon-only controls (see `tx-window-titlebar` pattern).
- Keep **keyboard** access for interactive controls; use native `<button>` for actions.

## Commits

- Follow the repository / user conventions for **`feat:`**, **`fix:`**, **`refactor:`** (see workspace user rules when committing).
